ZH: 今晚我们去吃涮锅。
EN: Tonight we are going to have hot pot.

ZH: 他喜欢在冬天吃涮羊肉。
EN: He likes to eat hotpot with lamb in the winter.

ZH: 她每周末都会要求家人一起涮火锅。
EN: She always asks her family to have hot pot together every weekend.

ZH: 你喜欢吃涮鱼还是涮牛肉？
EN: Do you prefer eating hot pot with fish or beef?

ZH: 近几年，在中国涮羊肉的食品文化越来越流行。
EN: In recent years, the food culture of eating hotpot with lamb in China has become more and more popular.

ZH: 我觉得吃火锅涮肉太油腻了。
EN: I think eating hot pot with meat is too greasy.

ZH: 在涮火锅时，别忘了提醒服务员把夹子借来。
EN: When eating hot pot, don't forget to ask the waitress for the clamp.

ZH: 每次去吃涮火锅，我们都会点一些蔬菜。
EN: Every time we go to eat hot pot, we always order some vegetables.

ZH: 你有试过在涮锅里加入豆腐吗？
EN: Have you ever tried adding tofu to the hot pot?

ZH: 在四川，火锅涮鱼是一种很受欢迎的美食。
EN: In Sichuan, hot pot with fish is a very popular delicacy.

ZH: 虽然吃涮火锅会很辣，但是我还是很喜欢。
EN: Although eating hot pot can be very spicy, I still like it.

ZH: 汤底是吃火锅时的重要元素之一。
EN: The broth is one of the important elements when eating hot pot.

ZH: 涮牛肉需要时间煮熟吗？
EN: Does it take time to cook hot pot with beef?

ZH: 在传统的火锅里，配菜有很多种。
EN: In traditional hot pot, there are many different side dishes.

ZH: 每次涮锅后，桌子上总是留下很多餐具。
EN: After every hot pot meal, there are always a lot of utensils left on the table.

ZH: 美国的火锅和中国的火锅有什么不同？
EN: What are the differences between American hot pot and Chinese hot pot?

ZH: 涮羊肉需要什么调味料？
EN: What seasoning do you need for hot pot with lamb?

ZH: 她邀请了朋友来家里涮火锅。
EN: She invited friends to her house to have hot pot.

ZH: 我能给你推荐一家很有名的涮锅店。
EN: I can recommend a famous hot pot restaurant to you.

ZH: 涮火锅是中国的传统饮食文化之一。
EN: Eating hot pot is one of the traditional food cultures in China.
